    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Slender spires rising from the ridge of a roof, most commonly from the roof intersection over the crossing of a church; use "crossing towers" for more substantial structures such as a lantern between spire and roof.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
